From f45f22516cdc1013dcaed84867fee9d14ba1d017 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: David Orman <ormandj@corenode.com>
Date: Fri, 10 Jul 2026 18:45:27 -0500
Subject: [PATCH] [Bugfix] Honor DeepSeek V4 checkpoints' MTP-layer
 compress_ratio entry (unscaled draft rope)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

DeepseekV4Attention maps every layer_id >= config.num_hidden_layers to
compress_ratio=1 on the assumption that the MTP draft layer is never
included in the checkpoint's compress_ratios list. DSpark-style
DeepSeek-V4 checkpoints DO carry an entry for the draft layer, with
value 0: uncompressed KV and plain (non-YaRN) rope. Forcing ratio 1
routes the draft through deepseek_yarn rope with positional geometry
the draft head was not trained with, and draft acceptance decays with
speculation depth.

Measured serving DeepSeek-V4-Flash-DSpark (mtp, 2x RTX PRO 6000 SM120,
TP=2): draft acceptance under load 57% -> 69%, with position-2
acceptance 0.275 -> 0.50 — the signature of a draft whose rope drifts
from the target as depth grows. (Measured with the full change; the
rope-type selection and the FP32 cache pin were not ablated
separately.)

Design: the raw checkpoint value is never stored as the operational
compress_ratio — KV-cache specs treat 1 as "no compression" and divide
by the ratio, so a stored 0 would be a sentinel leaking into an
operational invariant. resolve_layer_compress_ratio() clamps the
operational ratio to max(1, entry) and returns a separate
use_unscaled_rope flag that only affects rope construction:

- attention.py: draft layers that still index into compress_ratios
  take the checkpoint's entry (clamped); entry 0 selects unscaled rope.
  Layers beyond the list keep the ratio-1/yarn fallback, so checkpoints
  whose list stops at num_hidden_layers are unaffected. An explicit
  nonzero draft entry is now honored rather than forced to 1.
- common/rope.py: use_unscaled_rope selects rope_type "default".
  rope_parameters is copied before mutation — the previous in-place
  writes mutated the shared hf_config dict from every layer.
- common/rope.py: pin get_rope(dtype=torch.float32). The yarn path
  already re-registers its cos/sin cache as fp32; the default-rope path
  cast the cache to the ambient default dtype (bf16 when the draft
  initializes), and the DS4 kernels consume the cached table directly.

Tests cover the absent/zero/nonzero draft-entry matrix, rope class
selection for both paths, the no-shared-config-mutation invariant, and
the fp32 cache under a bf16 default dtype.

Ports local-inference-lab/vllm commits 03ede73f1d (Luke Alonso,
co-authored Martin Vit) and 1cb2260d4c (Martin Vit), redesigned to the
clamp+flag form.

Co-authored-by: Luke Alonso <lalonso@gmail.com>
Co-authored-by: Martin Vit <martin@voipmonitor.org>
Co-authored-by: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Signed-off-by: David Orman <ormandj@corenode.com>
